==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polysilicic
<hw>Pol`y*si*lic"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets> + <ets>silicic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to compounds formed by the condensation of two or
more molecules of silicic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Polysilicic acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>any
one of a series of acids formed by the condensation of two or more
molecules of silicic acid, with elimination of water.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polyspast</ent>⟦br⟧
